TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {2374=The 1964 Buffalo Bills season was the team’s fifth season. Buffalo won its first of two League Championships in the American Football League., 59483=Note: Tie games were not officially counted in the standings until 1972., 3043=The 1964 Bills' defense set an AFL record by giving up the fewest rushing yards in league history, with only 918, or 65.5 yards per game.[1] They also led the league in points allowed (242), total yards allowed (3,878), first downs surrendered (206), and rushing touchdowns allowed (four).[2]}
